.TH MRP 8 "2026-07-09" "OpenSRP" "System Manager's Manual"
.SH NAME
mrp \- command-line client for interrogating the mrpd REST API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mrp
.RI [ "global options" ]
.I protocol
.RI [ subcommand "] [" arguments ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mrp
is a command-line client that queries the REST management API of a running
.BR mrpd (8)
daemon and displays its MRP protocol state (MSRP streams and reservations, MVRP
VLAN registrations and MMRP group registrations). It is read\-only: it reports
state but does not modify reservations or configuration.
.PP
.B mrp
issues HTTP GET requests to the daemon at
.BI http:// host : port /api/avb
and formats the JSON response either as a human\-readable table (the default)
or as raw JSON.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.B mrp
requires an
.BR mrpd (8)
that was built with the
.B RestAPI
trait and started with
.B \-\-rest\-server\-port
(see
.BR mrpd (8)).
The
.B mrpd\-minimal
package omits the REST server and therefore does not ship or support
.BR mrp .
.PP
The tool is a Python 3 script and requires the
.B requests
library.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
These options precede the
.I protocol
argument.
.TP
.BI \-\-host " host"
Host running
.BR mrpd .
Default
.BR localhost .
.TP
.BI \-\-port " port"
TCP port of the
.B mrpd
REST API. Default
.BR 80 .
.TP
.B \-\-format " {table|json}"
Output format:
.B table
for a human\-readable table (default) or
.B json
for the raw API response.
.TP
.B \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit. May be given after a
.I protocol
or
.I subcommand
for command\-specific help.
.SH PROTOCOLS
Exactly one protocol argument is required.
.SS mrp
.B mrp mrp
.PP
Show general MRP status: the managed ports and their per\-port Leave times.
.SS msrp
.B mrp msrp
.I subcommand
.RB [ arg ]
.PP
Query the Multiple Stream Reservation Protocol. Subcommands:
.TP
.BI "port " [port]
With no argument, list all MSRP ports (one row per SR class per port, with
enabled / asCapable / forwarding status, domain boundary, applicant/registrar
state and SR PVID). With a
.I port
identifier (name or number), show that port in detail, including its Talker,
Failed Talker and Listener streams and its SR class parameters.
.TP
.BI "streams " [stream_id]
With no argument, list all MSRP streams (stream ID, destination, talker port
and type, VLAN, class/rank and bandwidth). With a
.I stream_id
argument, show that stream in detail, including its talker and per\-port
listeners.
.TP
.B listeners
List every MSRP listener across all streams (stream ID, port, type, connected
state and age).
.TP
.B talkers
List every MSRP talker across all streams (stream ID, port, advertised/failed
type and destination).
.SS mvrp
.B mvrp port
.RB [ port ]
.PP
Query the Multiple VLAN Registration Protocol. With no argument,
.B port
lists all MVRP ports and their registered VLAN counts. With a
.I port
identifier, show the VLANs on that port and their registered/declared state.
.SS mmrp
.B mmrp port
.RB [ port ]
.PP
Query the Multiple MAC Registration Protocol. With no argument,
.B port
lists all MMRP ports and their MAC address counts. With a
.I port
identifier, show the MAC addresses on that port and their registered/declared
state.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B mrp
exits non\-zero if it cannot connect to the daemon, receives an invalid
response, or is given invalid arguments.
.SH EXAMPLES
List all MSRP ports on the local daemon:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
mrp msrp port
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show a single stream in detail, as raw JSON:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
mrp --format json msrp streams 00:11:22:33:44:55:00:00
.fi
.RE
.PP
Query the MVRP VLANs on port
.B lan0
of a remote bridge:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
mrp --host br-01.example.net mvrp port lan0
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mrpd (8)
.PP
IEEE Std 802.1Q (clauses 10, 11, 35).
